The paper deals with improving error decoding of linear codes using machine learning concepts, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also introduces novel methods that incorporate active learning, which is a machine learning concept (cs.LG). The use of deep learning in error decoding also falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper deals with improving the decoding of communication blocks, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes guidelines for incorporating domain knowledge into deep learning models, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
